post_text: Good news for Gainesville R-V School District families. We have been notified that the food service program we utilized during the spring closure and summer school is once again available to us. We are so excited to let you know that we have been approved to serve all students free breakfast and lunch starting September 3, 2020. This program is through the USDA and will be available to us until the end of December 2020 or until the money for the program runs out. We are proud to partner with DHSS and the USDA to offer these free meals to our students in these stressful and uncertain times.

post_text: Tomorrow is our first summer school trip to the pool! In order to meet the regulations for a group our size to come before regular hours, all students must come to school before we go. We will be taking and recording temperature checks per the pool's policy. Additionally, please note parents cannot join us at the pool. This may change as regulations change throughout the summer, but for now students and staff only. Thank you for understanding. We're excited to provide this opportunity for our kids!!

post_text: We have added additional educational resources to the school's website. These include a reading log that can be used throughout the summer, a fun family tree activity, and a few STEM challenges to keep the creative juices flowing! These activities are fun for ANY age and serve as continued learning activities. post_text:
Gainesville R-V School District

March 16, 2020

Novel Coronavirus (COVID-19) Update

The Gainesville R-V School district would like to update parents and community members on measures being taken by the district as we monitor the spread and impact of the Novel Coronavirus (COVID-19). As we monitor the situation and review recommendations from federal, state, and local health officials, we have made the decision to extend Spring Break through Friday, April 3rd. This postponement includes all extra- and co-curricular activities, including athletic competitions, practices, and after-school programs and events. We will be following up with details regarding Meal Service and Instructional Plans in the coming days. This timeline would have students returning to school on Monday, April 6th. We will continue to monitor the situation, and gather input from state and local health officials.

As this situation continues to evolve, additional modifications may be necessary. As decisions are made, we will continue to share updated information as quickly as possible.

post_text: We are pleased to announce that we have received a STEM grant from The Curators of The University of Missouri on behalf of Missouri University of Science and Technology. This $10,000 grant will work to fund our existing STEM (Science, Technology, Engineering and Mathematics) efforts in both the Junior High and High School. The goal of this grant is to “enhance the educational opportunities for students by providing transformative learning experiences”. Thank you to Missouri S & T as well as State Representative Karla Eslinger for making this opportunity possible for our students.
text: We are pleased to announce that we have received a STEM grant from The Curators of The University of Missouri on behalf of Missouri University of Science and Technology. This $10,000 grant will work to fund our existing STEM (Science, Technology, Engineering and Mathematics) efforts in both the Junior High and High School. The goal of this grant is to “enhance the educational opportunities for students by providing transformative learning experiences”. Thank you to Missouri S & T as well as State Representative Karla Eslinger for making this opportunity possible for our students.

post_text: We would like to give a huge thank you and a shout out to the Missouri State Highway Patrol for taking time out to invest in our students this week. All of our 7th and 8th graders have been participating in Boating Licensing and Water Safety courses and will have an opportunity to get their boating licenses tomorrow! Water safety training just makes sense, especially when we live near so many beautiful lakes and rivers!

post_text:
Athletics Scheduling Updates!

1. The CC/Softball banquet has been rescheduled for Wednesday, November 20. Meal will be at 6:00 p.m. in the cafeteria with awards in the gym at approximately 6:30.

2.The annual Gainesville Bulldog Red/White Basketball Scrimmage and chili supper will be held Friday, November 22. The chili supper will begin at 5:00 p.m. Chili supper admittance will be by donation to the Athletic Booster Club. The evening activities will include: Lady Bulldog and Bulldog inter-squad scrimmage, peewee bulldog cheerleader performance, recognition of Junior High Bulldog basketball players, cheerleaders and JH/Elem cross country runners. These activities will begin at 6:00 p.m. Everyone is invited to attend and support our student athletes in preparation for the upcoming basketball season.

We appreciate our emergency organizations quick response and assistance with this incident.

post_text: The Gainesville R-5 School District Board of Education held a special board meeting for the purpose of interviewing the next superintendent of schools. The district is happy to announce that Justin Gilmore will be taking over the duties of superintendent effective July 1, 2020. Congratulations Mr. Gilmore!
